  <h1>About Puma</h1>
  <p>Puma is a globally recognized multinational corporation known for its athletic and casual footwear, sportswear, and accessories. The brand is famous for its fusion of sport and fashion, offering innovative and stylish products.</p>

  <h2>Key Highlights</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Puma was founded in 1948 in Germany by Rudolf Dassler, the brother of Adidas founder Adi Dassler.</li>
    <li>The brand's iconic logo, the Puma, represents agility, strength, and speed, reflecting the company's sporting spirit.</li>
    <li>Puma's product range includes popular items such as the Puma Suede sneakers, RS-X series, and collaborations with fashion designers and celebrities.</li>
    <li>Puma sponsors a wide array of athletes and sports teams, focusing on soccer, running, and motorsport, with endorsements from Usain Bolt and Neymar, among others.</li>
    <li>Puma is committed to sustainability and has introduced initiatives like the "Puma Forever Better" program, aiming to reduce its environmental footprint and promote social responsibility.</li>
  </ul>

